The paper deals with communication complexity, which is a topic in theoretical computer science and falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of the smooth-rectangle bound and information complexity bound suggests that the paper may also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The Tribes function is a well-known problem in computational complexity and may also be relevant to discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper's focus on randomized communication complexity and direct product theorems suggests that it may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG).
